{"title": "The Show Goes Hollywood", "content": "A sub-trope of Vacation Episode, where the characters visit Hollywood in Los Angeles, California.\n\nIt allows for potential celebrity cameos and advertising for the studio or network. Since most American movies and TV shows are created and/or filmed in the Greater Los Angeles Area of Southern California anyway, this trope allows the show to use actual locations in the GLAA (such as Hollywood) and other parts of Southern California instead of just faking other parts of the United States.\n\nIt frequently involves the characters getting temporary gigs in the entertainment industry (most commonly getting a role in a movie or TV show \u2014 or even both in some cases). It is likely a case of the writers writing what they know.\n\nSister trope of Aloha, Hawaii! and Viva Las Vegas!, which are two other major touristy areas in the USA. Compare Who Would Want to Watch Us? for the inverse situation (Hollywood comes to the characters to adapt their adventures into an in-universe movie or TV show).", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheShowGoesHollywood", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/GarfieldSpecials", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/FantasticFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SubMariner", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/IncredibleHulk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UltimateSpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MightyMouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Avengers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JayAndSilentBobStrikeBack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheViewAskewniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheThreeStooges", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Seinfeld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BoyMeetsWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MarriedWithChildren", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HappyDays", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ILoveLucy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Supernatural", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.